context.text: Rochester-Genesee Regional Transit Service - Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia
Numbers Manufacturer Model Type Year Length (ft) Width (in) Fuel/Power Overall Notes

As of right now, Nova Bus Classics , New Flyer D40LFs and D60LFs, NABI 40-LFWs, and Gillig Advantages are covering the streets of mass transit in Rochester . Most of these buses are equipped with a Detroit Diesel Series 50 or a Cummins ISL engine.
This is the complete table of buses RTS has operated for over the past 40 years.

As of June 2007, any bus that was equipped with a Detroit Diesel 6V92TA engine were gone from service. Earlier in the past, RTS were purchasing and opertating buses mostly from discontinued vehicle manufacturers such as General Motors and Flxible . They were also purchasing Gillig Phantom Suburbans and Orion Vs which are no longer present in Rochester , but are still present throughout the United States .
